parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear leaf spring can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on steep or rocky roads.
symptoms: The rear leaf spring breaks or fractures
causing the vehicle to sag or lose control
and potentially puncturing the gas tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on steep or rocky roads.
symptoms: The front lower A-frame (swing arm) fractures
and causing the vehicle to collapse onto the tire
potentially leading to a rollover crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-sway bar can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on steep or rocky roads.
symptoms: The anti-sway bar mounting clamp fails
causing the anti-sway bar to pummel the steel brake line
leading to a total loss of brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alignment issues can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on steep or rocky roads.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
and the steering wheel twists when driving over bumps or braking
indicating misalignment of the front end.
